@startuml 39-responsive-breakpoint-resize
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Responsive Breakpoint Resize

actor User
participant "Window\n(ResizeObserver)" as W
participant "BreakpointService" as BP
participant "AppShellComponent" as SHELL
participant "HomePage /\nSearchResultsPage /\nContactDetailPage /\nAskModePage" as PAGES
participant "SearchState /\nAskSessionService /\nSelectedContactService" as STATE

User -> W: resize window (XS -> LG)
W -> BP: breakpoint update
BP -> BP: signal.set('lg')
BP --> SHELL: (reactive)
SHELL -> SHELL: hide bottom-nav\nshow sidebar (>=MD)
SHELL --> User: chrome re-renders

BP --> PAGES: breakpoint = 'lg'
PAGES -> PAGES: computed layout = two-pane
PAGES -> STATE: read q, messages, selectedContact
STATE --> PAGES: same values
PAGES --> User: two-pane layout with\nsearch text / conversation / selection intact

note over STATE
  State lives in injectable
  services (Signals), not in
  per-component fields, so
  resize does not lose anything.
end note

@enduml
